Rabies, Italy: event summary
----------------------------
Start of event: 10 Oct 2008
Confirmation: 17 Oct 2008
Report date: 21 Oct 2008
Submission date: 21 Oct 2008
Reason: reoccurrence
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Number of outbreaks: 119
Date resolved: continuing
Epidemiological comments: this is the 1st case of sylvatic rabies in
Italy after 13 years and the infection may have been introduced in
Italy from the East.

[Since the submission of the immediate notification on 21 Oct 2008,
Italy has submitted 34 follow-up reports to the OIE, the most recent
on 2 Feb 2010 -- see item 2 below. All full reports, and an
interactive map, are accessible at the URL above. - Mod.AS]

